 courtesy of iCatCare, visit www.catcare4life.org for more information</fig=
caption></figure></div>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">How old is my cat?</h2>



<p>One of the most important things that we as cat owners can do is to appr=
eciate and understand how our cats develop and grow throughout their lives.=
 How can we tell what is =E2=80=98normal=E2=80=99 ageing vs. a sign of disc=
omfort or illness? This guide will help explain what you need to know to ke=
ep your cat happy and healthy no matter their age. Using the chart above, f=
ind out your cat=E2=80=99s age category and click on the relevant link belo=
w to learn more about your cat=E2=80=99s needs at their specific stage in l=
ife:</p>



